## Desired GraphQL Query

query InsurancePortfolio {
  account(id: "acct-1001") {
    id
    holderName
    accountType
    totalValue

    policies {
      policyNumber
      productName
      status

      linkedFunds {
        name
        assetClass
        oneYearReturnPercent
      }
    }

    fundHoldings {
      allocationPercent
      currentValue

      fund {
        name
        riskRating
        sustainabilityLabel
      }
    }
  }
}

## Expected Behaviour

Grafbase should automatically orchestrate these REST calls:

1. GET /accounts/acct-1001

2. GET /accounts/acct-1001/policies

3. For each policy fundId:
   GET /funds/{fundId}

4. For each account fundHolding fundId:
   GET /funds/{fundId}

Then merge all results into one GraphQL response.

## Important Constraints

- Do NOT modify any REST server code.
